{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a9b55cef-1c29-4b97-8623-2d274e092f65","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates **`.ips` crash reports** — no `createdump` needed.\n\n**Where to find them:**\n\n| Location | What's there |\n|---|---|\n| `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` | Your user's crash reports |\n| `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` | System-wide crash reports |\n\nLook for a file named like `YourApp-YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS.ips`.\n\n**Quick way to find it:**\n\n```bash\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/*.ips | head -5\n```\n\n**You can also use Console.app** → sidebar → \"Crash Reports\" to browse them with a GUI.\n\nThe `.ips` file contains the full native backtrace, register state, and loaded libraries — enough to symbolicate .NET runtime frames. If you need help symbolicating the crash report, let me know (I have a skill for that).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5389e326-1f88-4ed4-9810-0f3f9dded29d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, specifically when `createdump` isn't available. This is a diagnostic/troubleshooting question, not a code change request.\n\nOn macOS, when an app crashes, the system automatically generates crash reports. Let me provide the relevant information.","outputTokens":328,"requestId":"D7C3:1365D4:1BC163:2099EE:69F2B4E7"},"id":"39997d96-de80-4530-bc54-d69e41739a5d","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:48:33.273Z","parentId":"a256e81d-4328-4f8a-ab75-9dde89f1c6a1"}
